  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Create Virtual Tours to Share the Hiroshima Panels</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Maruki Gallery preserves memories of wartime atrocities and other forms of violence through the exhibition of the Hiroshima Panels. Iri and Toshi Maruki who jointly produced a series of 15 paintings opened the Gallery in 1967 hoping to capture visitors&apos; imagination and eventually prevent similar atrocities and invigorate people suffering in different contexts. This project will create virtual tours and footage to offer similar experiences to anyone around the world, present and future.</narrative>
  </description>
